---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

// Buttondown signup is the planned platform per BRAND_NOTES §6.
// While the integration is pending, this page is a placeholder
// that explains what's coming and offers the email-tip alternative.
// When the form is wired up, swap the placeholder section for a
// Buttondown form posting to the team's account.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Subscribe — DubaiPoints"
  description="The DubaiPoints brief: one email each Friday with the week's UAE salary-transfer changes, new card offers, and lifestyle deals. AED-first, no fluff. Per-band RSS feeds also available."
  fullWidth
>
  <article class="dp-article is-trust">
    <header class="dp-article-head">
      <p class="dp-article-eyebrow">Subscribe</p>
      <h1 class="dp-article-title">The Friday brief, in your inbox.</h1>
      <p class="dp-article-lede">
        One email each Friday with the week's salary-transfer changes, new
        card offers, miles redemptions worth knowing about, and lifestyle
        deals. AED-first, no fluff.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="dp-prose">
      <h2>Coming soon — sign-up is being wired up</h2>
      <p>
        The newsletter is on the launch list. The platform we're using
        (<a href="https://buttondown.email/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buttondown</a>) is a paid email service
        run by an independent founder; we picked it because it doesn't sell
        subscriber data and doesn't auto-redirect tracking links — both
        matter for a UAE-resident audience that gets enough surveillance
        already.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll get</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>One Friday-morning send with the week's UAE points / banking news.</li>
        <li>Per-band RSS feeds (5–8k, 8–15k, 15–30k, 30–50k, 50k+) so you only get the salary-transfer offers your band qualifies for.</li>
        <li>Time-bound deal alerts only when the deal is genuinely worth your time (we use the lifestyle-culture editor's judgement, not affiliate volume).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What you won't get</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Pop-up newsletter modals while you're trying to read.</li>
        <li>Affiliate links disguised as editorial picks.</li>
        <li>Sold or shared email addresses. Cloudflare Web Analytics is the only third-party measurement on the site, and it doesn't use cookies.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Until the integration ships</h2>
      <p>
        If you'd like to be on the list when it goes live, send a one-line
        email to <a href="mailto:info@dubaipoints.ae?subject=Newsletter">info@dubaipoints.ae</a>
        with the subject "<em>Newsletter</em>". We'll add you manually from
        a small holding list and migrate everyone over when the form goes
        live. No promotional content while you wait.
      </p>

      <h2>RSS already works</h2>
      <p>
        If you prefer RSS over email, the site-wide feed is at
        <a href="/rss.xml"><code>/rss.xml</code></a>. Per-band salary-transfer
        feeds will follow once the band landings ship — see the
        <a href="/editorial-policy/">editorial policy</a> for what we publish
        and how often.
      </p>

      <p class="related">
        <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial policy</a> ·
        <a href="/how-we-make-money/">How we make money</a> ·
        <a href="/about/">About DubaiPoints</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
